  "instructions": [
    "Combine flour, salt, and shortening in a mixing bowl and knead for 5 minutes.",
    "Gradually add water and knead for another 5 minutes until the dough is smooth.",
    "Allow the dough to rest for 1 hour in a warm place.",
    "Divide the dough into 12 equal pieces and roll each piece into a ball.",
    "Roll out each ball into a thin circle and brush with butter.",
    "Place a spoonful of fermented cabbage and caramelized onions in the center of each circle and brush the edges with egg wash.",
    "Fold the dough in half and press the edges together with a fork to seal the empanadas.",
    "Repeat the process with the remaining dough and filling.",
    "Fry the empanadas in hot oil until golden brown and crispy, about 3-4 minutes per side.",
    "Drain the empanadas on paper towels and serve hot.",
    "Garnish with chopped fresh cilantro and serve with a side of salsa or sour cream.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
